<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/3946695-claudia-staude"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1524050475i/3946695._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/3946695-claudia-staude">Claudia Staude</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It is fictional - however, the author did a great deal of research of the Asylum system and has a sister who is &quot;specially abled&quot; and deals with life <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It is fictional - however, the author did a great deal of research of the Asylum system and has a sister who is "specially abled" and deals with life on her own. I highly recommend reading her nonfiction work, "Riding the Bus with My Sister". It is delightful and it is how I found this author.<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
